Subject: part of
Value: a core relation that holds between a part and its whole@en

Subject: has part
Value: a core relation that holds between a whole and its part@en

Subject: journal article
Value: a report that is published in a journal@en

Subject: data item
Value: a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.@en

Subject: report
Value: a document assembled by an author for the purpose of providing information for the audience. A report is the output of a documenting process and has the objective to be consumed by a specific audience. Topic of the report is on something that has completed. A report is not a single figure. Examples of reports are journal article, patent application, grant progress report, case report (not patient record)@en

Subject: investigation
Value: a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

Subject: participates in
Value: a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process@en

Subject: has participant
Value: a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process@en

Subject: has input
Value: p has direct input c iff c is a participant in p, c is present at the start of p, and the state of c is modified during p.

Subject: has output
Value: p has output c iff c is a participant in p, c is present at the end of p, and c is not present at the beginning of p.

Subject: statistic
Value: a statistic is a measurement datum to describe a dataset or a variable. It is generated by a calculation on set of observed data.@en
